    "body": "### Problem\n\nI open a rust file (.rs) and do a change. write to the file. and try to redo, it says \"Already at newest change\".\r\n\r\nrust-analyzer somehow breaks the change history.\r\n\r\nI dont have this problem with eg. Golang (gopls).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI open a rust file (.rs) and do a change. write to the file. and try to redo, it says \"Already at newest change\".\r\n\r\nrust-analyzer somehow breaks the change history.\r\n\r\nI dont have this problem with eg. Golang (gopls).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nit should redo the changes after writing to the file.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno. vim behaves normal. I can redo in vim.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nAlpine Linux v3.20.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxterm 3.9.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAlpine Package Manager (APK)",
